5. Conclusions
The cooperation between the two courts of auditors has proved its worth.
It has thus been possible to gain the necessary knowledge of the systems used in both countries: in particular: • intra-Community transactions, • risk management at the USt, in particular with regard to the selection of risky transactions, • recovery of USt claims and • USt testing of large companies.
The audit revealed differences in the strategies for detecting USt fraud and in the systems explained above.
These findings can be used to improve existing procedures.
In addition, they can be used to initiate a discussion among the interested parties on which audit approaches and strategies can be used to combat fraud, e.g., the relationship within and between the Member States and the EU Commission.
The experience and knowledge gained should encourage the joint examination of the administration of the USt in the future.
